comments.content: "prima donna . . . a rather clever female-looking trick, who rates as a close double for the late Jean Malin, a pillar of this spot in the old days. Adams does a number Malin featured here."
Together with Lena Rivers, "Two of America's Foremost Female Impersonators"
At the venue for the past seven months
For legal name, see See 1938-07-30 The Billboard, Jul 30, 1938, 67 [Bert Peaches Buckingham, Baltimore]
Could not be Mitzi Mantis who had been murdered already.
"[with Lena Rivers,] female impersonators"; "Stillman and Rivers are the best of their kind in Kansas City. They received their usual good hand"
